WEBVTT

00:01.669 --> 00:03.904
You know what I love most
about being pregnant?

00:03.937 --> 00:05.506
Burgers for breakfast.

00:05.539 --> 00:06.974
Just today,

00:07.007 --> 00:08.676
because I woke up
craving red meat.

00:08.709 --> 00:10.978
Now, look away, baby.

00:11.011 --> 00:12.313
Mmm!

00:12.346 --> 00:13.514
Hi!
Hello!

00:13.547 --> 00:14.982
Oh, it's open.
Come in.
Oh.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.250
DAVID:
What is happening?

00:16.284 --> 00:17.985
Hello. Good morning.
Good morning.

00:18.018 --> 00:19.320
Hmm.
Goldie,

00:19.353 --> 00:20.754
what is in your mouth?

00:20.788 --> 00:21.922
Oh, my God, is that fast food?

00:21.955 --> 00:23.157
Oh, please tell me
you're bulimic

00:23.191 --> 00:24.825
so at least it'll come up
before it hits our baby.

00:24.858 --> 00:25.926
DAVID:
Or...

00:25.959 --> 00:27.995
you could eat this

00:28.028 --> 00:29.863
healthy, organic food

00:29.897 --> 00:32.100
we just got you
at the Farmers' Market.

00:32.133 --> 00:33.501
BRYAN:
I had never eaten broccoli

00:33.534 --> 00:35.703
before I met David.
Nutrition can be fun!

00:35.736 --> 00:37.371
Guys, pregnancy cravings
are totally normal,

00:37.405 --> 00:39.273
and it's just so delicious.

00:39.307 --> 00:41.442
Yeah, I know, but

00:41.475 --> 00:44.445
that delicious burger
could cause all kinds

00:44.478 --> 00:47.181
of developmental issues
for our baby.

00:47.215 --> 00:48.682
See, not a lot
of people know this,

00:48.716 --> 00:52.520
but charbroiled meat is a
carcinogen proven to effect DNA.

00:52.553 --> 00:55.356
Oh, well, I ate like this
when I was pregnant with Shania,

00:55.389 --> 00:56.790
and she turned
out just fine.

00:56.824 --> 00:58.859
Okay?

00:58.892 --> 00:59.860
BRYAN:
Um,

00:59.893 --> 01:01.195
also, uh,

01:01.229 --> 01:03.063
we brought your mail over
that was forwarded to our house.

01:03.097 --> 01:05.199
Oh.
Oh! What's this?

01:05.233 --> 01:07.201
It's your very important
absentee ballot

01:07.235 --> 01:09.036
from the crucial
battleground state of Ohio.

01:09.069 --> 01:11.705
Don't forget to mail that in.
It's a big election.

01:11.739 --> 01:12.873
I know. We're having

01:12.906 --> 01:14.708
a mock presidential election
at my school.

01:14.742 --> 01:16.310
BRYAN:
That's adorable.
I love mock things.

01:16.344 --> 01:17.411
DAVID:
No, you love

01:17.445 --> 01:18.579
to mock things.

01:18.612 --> 01:19.880
So, spill the
beans, kiddo.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.048
Who are you gonna vote for?

01:21.081 --> 01:23.251
Well, most of the kids
are just gonna vote

01:23.284 --> 01:24.918
for whoever
their parents do,

01:24.952 --> 01:26.420
but I'm thinking
about voting Obama.

01:26.454 --> 01:29.590
Well, if you do the math
on that,

01:29.623 --> 01:31.892
that means your
mom is voting

01:31.925 --> 01:33.561
for... O.M.G.O.P!

01:33.594 --> 01:35.496
Mitt Romney? You
can't be serious.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.565
Goldie, you are carrying
our Democratic baby.

01:37.598 --> 01:39.400
Our beautiful
little donkey fetus.

01:39.433 --> 01:41.001
Maybe you guys should just steal
my ballot and vote for me.

01:41.034 --> 01:42.736
That's what my nana did in 2008.

01:42.770 --> 01:44.905
That is outrageous.
She can't do that.

01:44.938 --> 01:46.407
Yeah, this is America, damn it.

01:46.440 --> 01:47.575
You're free to vote

01:47.608 --> 01:49.910
for the black incumbent
president of our choice.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.011
Hmm.

02:18.138 --> 02:20.308
What's Smelly eating?

02:20.341 --> 02:22.210
Vegetables.

02:22.243 --> 02:24.878
You stay out
of my granddaughter's head!

02:24.912 --> 02:27.281
I put years into shaping it,
and I will not have

02:27.315 --> 02:29.817
you left-wing Nancy boys
poisoning her

02:29.850 --> 02:31.885
with your hug-a-Muslim
bull crap!

02:31.919 --> 02:34.955
Mrs. Forrest,
what a disturbing surprise.

02:34.988 --> 02:37.791
I will have you know
that my family has voted

02:37.825 --> 02:39.159
Republican since
Abraham Lincoln,

02:39.193 --> 02:41.729
the freer of the slaves.

02:41.762 --> 02:43.664
I am proud of my party,
and I have been

02:43.697 --> 02:46.133
a supporter since 1972.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.068
ALL (chanting):
No more war!
(car horn honking)

02:48.101 --> 02:50.304
Dick Nixon knows how
to keep America strong!

02:50.338 --> 02:51.972
That's why
I like Dick.

02:52.005 --> 02:52.973
Who is with me?

02:53.006 --> 02:55.343
I like Dick!
I like Dick!

02:55.376 --> 02:59.413
Oh, so we have you to thank for
Watergate and Reagan and Bush

02:59.447 --> 03:00.581
and baby Bush.

03:00.614 --> 03:01.749
Oh, honey,

03:01.782 --> 03:03.651
even we don't like
the Bushes anymore.

03:03.684 --> 03:05.419
But you're voting
for Mitt Romney,

03:05.453 --> 03:07.255
which is the
equivalent of saying

03:07.288 --> 03:09.323
the poor aren't entitled
to health care,

03:09.357 --> 03:11.992
or the environment
doesn't need protecting.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.262
Mitt Romney is interested
in preserving

03:14.295 --> 03:15.663
every American's right

03:15.696 --> 03:19.667
to make his or her own choices.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.335
Unless you're gay.

03:21.369 --> 03:24.338
I thought
gay wasn't a choice.

03:24.372 --> 03:28.041
You've already polluted Goldie's
womb with your gay sperms.

03:28.075 --> 03:29.176
Leave her vote alone.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.611
You know what I
think this is about?

03:30.644 --> 03:32.680
Obama is black, and
you don't like anybody

03:32.713 --> 03:34.214
who's not like you.

03:34.248 --> 03:36.216
Oh, I would slap your face
right now

03:36.250 --> 03:39.186
if I didn't want to get
a handful of man makeup.

03:39.219 --> 03:40.288
It is tinted sunscreen!

03:40.321 --> 03:41.689
DAVID:
I'm just gonna say it.

03:41.722 --> 03:45.526
Mrs. Forrest, I believe
you are a racist.

03:45.559 --> 03:48.562
Why is that the place
that all you liberals go to?

03:48.596 --> 03:51.198
Just because
I don't like a man

03:51.231 --> 03:53.801
who wants to take
my hard-earned money

03:53.834 --> 03:57.638
and dump it into
a broken system, I'm a racist?

03:57.671 --> 03:59.707
Don't you think
it's a little more racist

03:59.740 --> 04:03.411
to vote for a black man
simply because he's black?

04:05.078 --> 04:06.647
And what about you two?

04:06.680 --> 04:09.717
I don't imagine you're lighting
candles on Kwanzaa.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.051
Couple of hypocrites.

04:11.084 --> 04:12.386
Like every other liberal,

04:12.420 --> 04:14.888
you walk the walk,
but you can't talk the talk.

04:14.922 --> 04:17.491
That is not true! We have black
friends. We have oodles of them!

04:17.525 --> 04:19.159
Right.
We do, and if you
don't believe me,

04:19.192 --> 04:20.728
you can come to our
party on Friday night,

04:20.761 --> 04:21.929
and you can meet
them for yourself.

04:21.962 --> 04:23.997
Mm.
Great. I'll see you

04:24.031 --> 04:27.234
and all your homies on Friday.

04:27.267 --> 04:30.070
Great!

04:30.103 --> 04:32.573
So, we're having a party?

04:32.606 --> 04:34.575
Yup.

04:34.608 --> 04:35.943
Know any black people?

04:35.976 --> 04:38.746
How is it that we don't have
any black friends?

04:38.779 --> 04:40.448
Oh, David, we
have black friends.

04:40.481 --> 04:42.015
Like who?
Amir.

04:42.049 --> 04:43.917
Amir is not black.
He's Indian.

04:43.951 --> 04:46.420
He's of a hue.
(laughs)

04:46.454 --> 04:47.588
Mrs. Forrest is right.

04:47.621 --> 04:48.989
We are phony,
liberal frauds.

04:49.022 --> 04:50.257
We are racists!

04:50.290 --> 04:51.825
We can't be.

04:51.859 --> 04:55.529
We are two educated,
successful, enlightened gay men.

04:55.563 --> 04:56.997
I guess we can't be held
entirely responsible.

04:57.030 --> 04:58.466
We do meet a lot
of black people.

04:58.499 --> 05:00.100
Right.
We see them at work.

05:00.133 --> 05:01.769
Uh-uh.
We run into them
at parties,

05:01.802 --> 05:03.270
except for our own.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.872
I mean, is it our fault
that none of them stick?

05:04.905 --> 05:08.376
Yeah, using the pejorative
"them" is not helping our case.

05:08.409 --> 05:10.944
We have to get some black
people to come to our party.

05:10.978 --> 05:12.446
I will not be
called a bigoted,

05:12.480 --> 05:13.781
armchair liberal by anyone.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.649
Maybe I could get the
cast of Treme to come.

05:15.683 --> 05:17.451
I sat next to them at the
Golden Globes last year,

05:17.485 --> 05:19.019
and since nobody watches
that show anyway,

05:19.052 --> 05:22.089
they could easily pass as your
run-of-the-mill, non-famouses.

05:25.759 --> 05:27.628
Rocky, there you are.

05:27.661 --> 05:30.330
Bryan's coming down to
approve Clea's wardrobe.

05:30.364 --> 05:31.732
He has nixed everything
I've shown him.

05:31.765 --> 05:34.134
