Law & Order, but no.

08:41.121 --> 08:43.390
No. You are just
the long-time contemporary

08:43.423 --> 08:44.758
of a very successful

08:44.792 --> 08:46.760
color-indifferent,
TV writer/producer.

08:46.794 --> 08:48.428
And you're playing
opposite the guest

08:48.461 --> 08:49.763
who just arrived.

08:49.797 --> 08:51.098
She's playing
a very racist woman

08:51.131 --> 08:52.766
who doesn't believe
that I have black friends.

08:52.800 --> 08:54.301
And action!

08:55.268 --> 08:57.771
Excuse me. Ah,
Mrs. Forrest.

08:57.805 --> 08:59.607
Welcome. So happy
you're here.

08:59.640 --> 09:02.109
Oh, can the coffee klatch,
Marge. Where are the blacks?

09:02.142 --> 09:03.944
The blacks? Well,

09:03.977 --> 09:05.378
if you listen carefully,

09:05.412 --> 09:07.615
you can hear them in the
fields singing spirituals.

09:07.648 --> 09:08.949
Ooh, look. There's one.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.751
But she's not really
a friend, is she,

09:10.784 --> 09:12.786
because she works
for the missus?
(laughs)

09:12.820 --> 09:14.187
Hi, Nana.
Ah.

09:14.221 --> 09:16.256
Oh, Goldie, you're 24 years old.

09:16.289 --> 09:18.592
Would it kill you
to put on a little lipstick?

09:18.626 --> 09:19.860
Where's the kid?

09:19.893 --> 09:22.963
Oh, she's upstairs writing
Charlie Rose fan fiction.

09:22.996 --> 09:25.098
I'm gonna grab a soda.
Or... (clears throat)

09:25.132 --> 09:26.466
Even healthier
than a soda.

09:26.499 --> 09:28.301
Have you tried
coconut water?

09:28.335 --> 09:30.203
Come on, I'll show you.

09:30.237 --> 09:31.605
Mrs. Forrest, mingle.

09:31.639 --> 09:33.774
It's what us humans do.

09:33.807 --> 09:34.942
Well, well, well,
Jane Forrest.

09:34.975 --> 09:37.244
I'd like you to meet a
dear, dear friend of mine

09:37.277 --> 09:39.212
from way, way back.

09:39.246 --> 09:43.316
