four times as much.

11:38.866 --> 11:39.767
Goldie.

11:39.800 --> 11:41.134
Oh, great, thank you.
Delicious.

11:41.969 --> 11:42.936
Fruit.

11:42.970 --> 11:44.104
Why are you
being punished?

11:44.137 --> 11:47.775
Oh, they just know
I'm allergic to crust.

11:47.808 --> 11:50.010
(laughs)
And deliciousness.

11:50.043 --> 11:51.444
(coughs)

11:51.478 --> 11:52.579
AMIR:
Honey, you okay?

11:52.612 --> 11:55.849
Fine, just, cake went
down the wrong way.

11:55.883 --> 11:58.786
Well, fortunately you have
two doctors at the table,

11:58.819 --> 12:00.754
so choke all you want.
We are on the job.

12:00.788 --> 12:02.455
Yeah, so long as you have
health insurance.

12:02.489 --> 12:04.124
(laughter)

12:04.157 --> 12:05.458
Well, unless Romney wins,

12:05.492 --> 12:07.360
and then we'll just have
to sit here and watch you die.

12:07.394 --> 12:08.695
JANE:
Oh, you liberals.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.764
You sure do love to twist
the truth, don't you?

12:10.798 --> 12:12.132
Oh, that's right, everybody,

12:12.165 --> 12:15.102
we have a real, live Republican
at the table here tonight.

12:15.135 --> 12:17.537
Quick, everyone show
proof of citizenship.

12:17.570 --> 12:18.705
(laughter)

12:18.738 --> 12:19.940
So, Jane,

12:19.973 --> 12:22.209
you don't think all
Americans are entitled

12:22.242 --> 12:23.811
to affordable health care?
If you can find

12:23.844 --> 12:25.979
affordable health care,
more power to you.

12:26.013 --> 12:28.281
I just don't want
the federal government

12:28.315 --> 12:29.983
making decisions
that are

12:30.017 --> 12:31.451
my choice to make.

12:31.484 --> 12:33.153
Unless it's a woman's
right to choose.

12:33.186 --> 12:35.388
Yeah, or the right to
marry whomever you love.

12:35.422 --> 12:36.556
You know, by
all means,

12:36.589 --> 12:38.658
vote for your pet projects

12:38.691 --> 12:39.893
over the good

12:39.927 --> 12:40.994
of the entire country.

12:41.028 --> 12:43.163
Uh, equality is not
a pet project.

12:43.196 --> 12:44.631
It's actually
a moral imperative.

12:44.664 --> 12:46.733
Look, Obama's plan
might not have been perfect,

12:46.766 --> 12:48.301
but at least he tried
coming up with a fix.

12:48.335 --> 12:49.336
Yeah.
JANE:
Yeah, by making me pay

12:49.369 --> 12:52.339
every time some illegal
sprains his ankle

12:52.372 --> 12:53.173
jumping the border.

12:53.206 --> 12:54.174
This chocolate pie

12:54.207 --> 12:55.675
is delicious, by the way.

12:55.708 --> 12:58.078
Thank you, I
made it myself.
(Bryan laughs)

12:58.111 --> 12:59.512
Your whole system
is broke,

12:59.546 --> 13:01.481
and your Obama just
wants to keep dumping

13:01.514 --> 13:03.016
more money into it.
It's like giving

13:03.050 --> 13:05.986
penicillin to a Kardashian--
too little, too late.

13:06.019 --> 13:07.487
That's good.
So it's just
about money to you?

13:07.520 --> 13:08.856
No, it isn't
just about money.

13:08.889 --> 13:11.191
It's about personal
responsibility,

13:11.224 --> 13:14.161
and personal responsibility
begins at home.

13:14.194 --> 13:16.763
I run my house the way
the government should be run.

13:16.796 --> 13:17.931
Goldie pays rent.

13:17.965 --> 13:19.199
There are no handouts,

13:19.232 --> 13:20.533
there's no
freeloading.

13:20.567 --> 13:23.203
And the way you talk about
a woman's right to choose--

13:23.236 --> 13:25.505
if I hadn't taken away
her mother's right,

13:25.538 --> 13:26.606
she wouldn't
be sitting

13:26.639 --> 13:28.108
with us while we sip Amaretto

13:28.141 --> 13:30.043
around this table

13:30.077 --> 13:31.111
at the penis palace.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.379
Oh, yeah,

13:32.412 --> 13:36.516
that's right, 25 years ago
my prize of a daughter,

13:36.549 --> 13:38.018
She-Who-Shall-
Not-Be-Named,

13:38.051 --> 13:40.387
was headed
for the abortion clinic

13:40.420 --> 13:42.222
and I took away

13:42.255 --> 13:44.124
her right to choose.

13:44.157 --> 13:45.458
I forced her to take
responsibility

13:45.492 --> 13:47.394
for her actions.

13:47.427 --> 13:49.462
We would not be having
this rousing political debate,

13:49.496 --> 13:52.565
trying to sway
Goldie's vote

13:52.599 --> 13:55.702
because Goldie wouldn't be here.

13:55.735 --> 13:57.237
How can you say that
right in front of her?

13:57.270 --> 13:58.405
Oh, no, it's okay.

13:58.438 --> 14:00.573
She tells me that story
every year on my birthday.

14:00.607 --> 14:01.574
So, who wants more wine?

14:01.608 --> 14:03.076
I'll get it.
Yes, me.

14:03.110 --> 14:06.746
(overlapping chatter)

14:06.779 --> 14:09.216
This is a disaster.

14:09.249 --> 14:11.051
I can't believe we're trying
to impress this woman.
Shh...

14:11.084 --> 14:13.320
What are you
shush-shush-shush?
Look,

14:13.353 --> 14:16.256
I-I think I may have offended
some of your friends

14:16.289 --> 14:19.759
back there inadvertently
with my passion.

14:19.792 --> 14:20.760
I'm sorry.

14:20.793 --> 14:24.197
Oh, well... thank you very much.

14:24.231 --> 14:25.498
It was a
little harsh.

14:25.532 --> 14:27.935
I think this might be a great
time to change the mood.

14:27.968 --> 14:29.369
I bet your friends
would be thrilled

14:29.402 --> 14:31.104
to hear some happy news,

14:31.138 --> 14:32.672
like you and Sissy
are going to be mommies.

14:32.705 --> 14:33.907
Hmm, I don't know.
Oh, no, David's,

14:33.941 --> 14:35.175
David's superstitious.
Yeah.

14:35.208 --> 14:37.110
He wants to wait to announce
till the 12th week.

14:37.144 --> 14:39.947
You've got all your friends
together in one place.

14:39.980 --> 14:41.348
You're at the ten-week mark,

14:41.381 --> 14:43.183
out of the woods.
I think it would make

14:43.216 --> 14:44.784
the party memorable.

14:44.817 --> 14:46.819
Think about it.

14:48.721 --> 14:50.690
CLINT:
What are you doing
tomorrow night?

14:50.723 --> 14:52.092
Want to go
to a movie?

14:52.125 --> 14:54.928
Oh, um, yeah,
that sounds fun.

14:54.962 --> 14:56.129
(glass clinks)

14:56.163 --> 14:58.031
So, since you are

14:58.065 --> 14:59.532
all our closest
friends--

14:59.566 --> 15:01.334
except you...

15:01.901 --> 15:03.036
...and you and you,

15:03.070 --> 15:04.037
now seems

15:04.071 --> 15:07.207
like the perfect time
to tell you

15:07.240 --> 15:08.976
that Bryan and I

15:09.009 --> 15:10.377
are pregnant.

15:10.410 --> 15:13.780
(laughter)
Thank you,
thank you.

15:13.813 --> 15:16.449
We are ten weeks along
with our baby

15:16.483 --> 15:18.485
and we could
not be happier.

15:18.518 --> 15:20.587
And we could not
have done this

15:20.620 --> 15:22.389
without our
amazing surrogate

15:22.422 --> 15:24.457
Goldie, so,
Goldie...

15:24.491 --> 15:25.492
A toast to Goldie.

15:25.525 --> 15:27.160
DAVID:
Cheers.

15:27.194 --> 15:28.795
You're pregnant
with their baby?

15:28.828 --> 15:31.798
Oh, wait, Shania really
should be here for this.

15:31.831 --> 15:32.799
Shania is Goldie's daughter

15:32.832 --> 15:34.334
from her crumbling
marriage.

15:35.202 --> 15:37.870
Excuse me, please.

15:41.941 --> 15:43.310
What?

15:48.615 --> 15:49.616
I have got to get out of here.

15:49.649 --> 15:52.986
I am so sick of you all
crapping your $400 jeans

15:53.020 --> 15:54.587
over this Obama.

15:54.621 --> 15:55.922
Don't lump me in with them.

15:55.955 --> 15:58.258
Oh, excuse me, $20 jeans.

15:58.291 --> 15:59.426
I'm voting for Romney.

15:59.459 --> 16:00.427
What?

16:00.460 --> 16:01.761
You done lost your damn mind.

16:01.794 --> 16:04.664
Wow, a black Republican.

16:04.697 --> 16:06.466
You know,
I've heard stories.

16:06.499 --> 16:07.967
I just never knew
they were real.

16:08.001 --> 16:10.303
How can you turn your back
on Barack right now?

16:10.337 --> 16:11.304
I don't vote race.

16:11.338 --> 16:12.639
I vote issues,

16:12.672 --> 16:14.474
and I think Romney's
experience as a businessman is

16:14.507 --> 16:16.676
the thing we need to get
this economy moving.

16:16.709 --> 16:17.844
Goldie isn't answering.

16:17.877 --> 16:19.146
I think I might call the cops.

16:19.179 --> 16:21.181
You are not sending
a policeman to chase down

16:21.214 --> 16:23.783
a hormonal girl's
temper tantrums.

16:23.816 --> 16:24.951
I'll track her
myself.

16:24.984 --> 16:26.153
Yeah, why don't you hop
on your broomstick

16:26.186 --> 16:29.522
and write "Surrender Goldie"
over the Hollywood skies?

16:29.556 --> 16:31.624
Was that an actual
Judy Garland reference?

16:31.658 --> 16:34.127
I'm surprised you're not
wearing ruby slippers.

16:34.161 --> 16:35.128
Keep joking, lady.

16:35.162 --> 16:36.296
It's your manipulations

16:36.329 --> 16:37.864
that made her run off
in the first place.

16:37.897 --> 16:40.167
My manipulations, mine?
Yeah.

16:40.200 --> 16:43.336
This party is a bigger farce
than Tom Cruise's marriage

16:43.370 --> 16:45.038
to that girl
with the dead eyes.

16:45.072 --> 16:46.306
Which one?

16:46.339 --> 16:48.308
Okay, uh, this is getting weird,

16:48.341 --> 16:49.342
and, uh,

16:49.376 --> 16:50.510
my catering shift ended
an hour ago,

16:50.543 --> 16:51.878
so...

16:51.911 --> 16:54.214
I think we can both agree
that I nailed it.

16:54.247 --> 16:55.848
Call my people.

16:55.882 --> 16:56.849
I knew it.

16:56.883 --> 16:58.685
He's an actor.

16:58.718 --> 16:59.719
He was a black actor.

16:59.752 --> 17:01.321
Farce.
A blactor.
Enough, hey!

17:01.354 --> 17:03.990
The important thing
is that we find Goldie.

17:04.023 --> 17:05.858
Now, where the hell
could she be?

17:05.892 --> 17:07.694
I think I might
know where she is.

17:10.530 --> 17:14.067
See, told you
she'd be here.

17:16.603 --> 17:18.538
Hey, hey, order me a double
cheeseburger and fries

17:18.571 --> 17:19.872
but say it's for you.

17:19.906 --> 17:21.208
I'll eat it cold, crouched
behind the potting bench

17:21.241 --> 17:22.742
in the garage after
David falls asleep.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.777
Your secret's
safe with me.

17:28.915 --> 17:31.551
Goldie, we are so sorry.

17:31.584 --> 17:33.353
We had no right to
announce the pregnancy

17:33.386 --> 17:35.255
before talking
to you first.

17:35.288 --> 17:36.589
And the food.

17:36.623 --> 17:39.226
David was so controlling
about the food.

17:39.259 --> 17:40.360
JANE:
Oh, come on,

17:40.393 --> 17:42.695
you know the real reason
you ran off is because

17:42.729 --> 17:44.464
Wayland and Madame here
were trying to sway your vote

17:44.497 --> 17:46.099
and keep that man
in the Brown House.

17:46.133 --> 17:48.235
(crying)

17:48.268 --> 17:50.203
No, no, no, no, you
can have the burger.

17:50.237 --> 17:52.071
Here, eat, finish the burger.
BRYAN:
Yeah, yeah, le-le-let's

17:52.105 --> 17:53.473
get you some chili,
too, I mean,

17:53.506 --> 17:55.542
I mean, if, if,
if you want chili.

17:55.575 --> 17:57.076
That's right.

17:57.110 --> 17:59.146
We still might
make suggestions,

17:59.179 --> 18:01.881
but if you want to eat
chili, you can eat chili.

18:01.914 --> 18:04.617
I'm sorry for being
so emotional, guys.

18:04.651 --> 18:05.652
It's just that I thought

18:05.685 --> 18:07.554
that moving out here,
changing everything,

18:07.587 --> 18:09.122
that my life
was finally going

18:09.156 --> 18:12.259
to be my own,
but it's not.

18:12.292 --> 18:14.093
Clay is suing me
for custody.

18:14.127 --> 18:15.295
This paper says

18:15.328 --> 18:17.797
I got to take Shania
back to Ohio.

18:21.434 --> 18:22.435
Hallelujah.

18:22.469 --> 18:23.970
That moron
finally did

18:24.003 --> 18:25.605
one smart thing.

18:25.638 --> 18:27.140
Okay, okay.

18:31.311 --> 18:33.313
(school bell rings)

18:38.485 --> 18:39.786
Hey.
Hey.

18:39.819 --> 18:41.788
So who'd you vote for?

18:41.821 --> 18:42.822
Well, I was
leaning

18:42.855 --> 18:44.624
Romney for a while
because he seems

18:44.657 --> 18:46.459
more committed to
Israel's security,

18:46.493 --> 18:47.694
but Obama believes
gay people

18:47.727 --> 18:49.329
should be treated
like human beings,

18:49.362 --> 18:50.663
and you guys are gay,

18:50.697 --> 18:53.633
so that made me
vote for him.

18:53.666 --> 18:55.101
Yes.
I feel like we're
watching her

18:55.134 --> 18:56.636
take her first steps.
Yeah.

18:56.669 --> 18:59.172
Hey, Shania, want to
help me pull my lever?

18:59.206 --> 19:00.440
Okay.

19:00.473 --> 19:02.309
Hey, let's save that for your
first term in Congress, kid.

19:02.342 --> 19:03.443
Off you go.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.278
So, Goldie,
how are you going to vote?

19:05.312 --> 19:07.347
Like daughter,
like mother?
Hmm?

19:07.380 --> 19:09.249
Meh.

19:11.017 --> 19:13.019
What, you haven't decided
who to vote for yet?

19:13.052 --> 19:14.321
A billion dollars in ads...

19:14.354 --> 19:15.955
I didn't say I don't know
who I'm voting for.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.123
I'm just not
telling you.

19:17.156 --> 19:18.958
Isn't that the whole point
of a true democracy?

19:18.991 --> 19:21.694
Well played.

19:22.529 --> 19:23.796
And we will
honor that.

19:23.830 --> 19:26.399
Blink once for Obama,
twice for the Mormon.

19:26.433 --> 19:27.434
(laughs)

19:34.541 --> 19:36.008
You know, it would be nice
to have more diversity

19:36.042 --> 19:38.711
in our lives--
if not for us, for the baby.

19:38.745 --> 19:39.512
It's true.

19:39.546 --> 19:40.847
Growing up with two white dads.

19:40.880 --> 19:43.049
I mean, how much travel
and culture and dance

19:43.082 --> 19:44.050
can one kid take?

19:44.083 --> 19:45.218
I'm serious.

19:45.252 --> 19:47.520
I know, I know, and I agree.

19:47.554 --> 19:50.189
I mean, we talk the talk, but
we don't always walk the walk.

19:52.058 --> 19:53.159
Not a word to
your grandmother.

19:53.192 --> 19:55.528
We will deny it,
I swear.

19:55.562 --> 19:56.896
You know, it's never too late.

19:56.929 --> 19:59.599
Come on.

20:04.571 --> 20:07.240
Um, hi, I'm Goldie,
Shania's mom.

20:07.274 --> 20:08.375
I'm Renee.

20:08.408 --> 20:10.377
This is my husband Joe
and our son Matthew.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.544
So, how far
along are you?

20:11.578 --> 20:12.712
Almost six months.

20:12.745 --> 20:14.113
GOLDIE:
Oh, congratulations.

20:14.146 --> 20:17.250
I'm not showing yet
but, um, I'm pregnant, too.

20:17.284 --> 20:18.551
Oh, congratulations to you.

20:18.585 --> 20:20.587
Oh, well, thank-- um, actually
it's, it's not my baby.

20:21.288 --> 20:22.455
It's theirs.

20:22.489 --> 20:24.524
I'm their surrogate.
(Joe chuckles)

20:24.557 --> 20:27.059
You know, we've
done this before.

20:27.093 --> 20:29.228
If you have questions about
being first-time parents,

20:29.262 --> 20:30.430
we should have
dinner sometime.

20:30.463 --> 20:31.564
Uh, we would love that.

20:31.598 --> 20:32.865
Yeah, that'd be great.

20:32.899 --> 20:34.066
Thanks.
GOLDIE:
Cool.

20:34.100 --> 20:35.402
Nice meeting you.
See you.

20:35.435 --> 20:36.536
This is perfect.

20:36.569 --> 20:38.905
You were just saying
we need some gay friends.

20:39.906 --> 20:41.808
(indistinct chatter)

20:41.841 --> 20:43.843
(all laughing)

20:48.915 --> 20:51.384
Okay, who would you vote for,
SpongeBob or Dora the Explorer?

20:51.418 --> 20:53.386
I think SpongeBob
would definitely push through

20:53.420 --> 20:55.888
gay marriage, and Dora is
better at foreign policy.

20:55.922 --> 20:58.057
Plus it'd be a landslide
with the Latino vote.

20:58.090 --> 21:00.427
I have one--
Easter Bunny or Santa Claus?

21:00.460 --> 21:03.896
Uh, Santa-- I think he uses
illegals to make those toys,

21:03.930 --> 21:05.998
but the Easter Bunny--
I mean, we never even see him.

21:06.032 --> 21:06.999
What's he hiding?

21:07.033 --> 21:08.301
Easter eggs?

21:08.335 --> 21:10.437
I still think he should release
his tax returns.

